---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import NextReleaseBadge from '../components/NextReleaseBadge.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Release notes" description="What's new in tflo: hardening pass through Phase 6.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20">
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">
      Release notes
    </h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-text-muted mb-3 leading-relaxed">
      tflo is pre-1.0 and not yet on crates.io &mdash; consume via git. The blocks below
      summarize what's on the <code>hardening-pass</code> branch awaiting a tagged release.
      Canonical changelog:
      <a href="https://github.com/matt-cochran/tflo/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md" class="text-primary hover:underline">CHANGELOG.md</a>.
    </p>
    <p class="text-text-muted mb-12 leading-relaxed">
      <NextReleaseBadge variant="block" /> Items below ship at the next release.
    </p>

    <!-- tflo-cep + tflo-cep-wasm -->
    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3"><code>tflo-cep</code> + <code>tflo-cep-wasm</code> &mdash; event-pattern matching</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Two new sibling crates that compose typed signals into multi-event domain
        signals &mdash; "abandoned cart" (added to cart, not purchased within T),
        "engaged with product" (viewed, then scrolled deep within T), "rage click"
        (three identical clicks within T). Six-method closure-based builder
        mirroring <code>tflo-cel</code> / <code>tflo-rhai</code> / <code>tflo-rego</code>;
        bounded by construction.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">
        A generic <code>engine::Runtime</code> parameterized over three callback traits
        (<code>Predicate</code>, <code>EmitCallback</code>, <code>TimestampCallback</code>)
        is the <em>single</em> implementation of the matching state machine.
        <code>tflo-cep</code> wraps it with Arc-based, <code>Send + Sync</code> callbacks
        for multi-threaded Rust use; <code>tflo-cep-wasm</code> wraps it with Rc-based,
        <code>js_sys::Function</code> callbacks for the browser.
        <strong class="text-white">No duplicate runtime.</strong> Feature additions land
        once. See the <a href="/docs/patterns" class="text-primary hover:underline">event patterns</a> docs.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        The companion TypeScript SDK
        <a href="https://github.com/matt-cochran/tflo-browser-events" class="text-primary hover:underline"><code>@tflo/browser-events</code></a>
        ships a capture layer (DOM listeners + <code>IntersectionObserver</code>-backed
        viewport tracking), a pluggable <code>Sink</code> interface (Console, Edge, GA4
        bundled; custom sinks in fifty lines), a consent gate, and end-of-session
        flush via <code>sendBeacon</code>. Total wire weight: ~25 KB gzip. The
        <a href="/docs/browser-analytics" class="text-primary hover:underline">browser analytics</a>
        page walks through the workflow end-to-end.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Phase 0 / CEP refactor -->
    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">CEP reorientation</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">
        tflo reframed from a financial TA library into a generic temporal event-processing
        engine. The <code>CustomNode</code> plugin system unified into a single
        <code>Operator</code> trait; dual-use operators
        (<code>deviation_band</code>, <code>peak_decline</code>, <code>rate_of_change</code>,
        <code>momentum</code>, <code>zscore</code>) reframed as domain-neutral. Finance
        moved to <code>tflo-fintech</code> as one plugin among many. All 25 examples
        reskinned across 14 domains.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- tflo-ops split -->
    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3"><code>tflo-ops</code> &mdash; operator catalog split</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        Operators moved out of <code>tflo-core</code> into a dedicated
        <code>tflo-ops</code> crate. Core is now engine-only: record sources, closure
        transforms, the <code>Operator</code> plugin trait, keyed execution, checkpointing.
        <code>tflo-ops</code> owns every windowed aggregation, statistical operator,
        stateful tracker, and event detector. New <code>NodeOutput</code> public type
        supports both the f64 hot path and typed non-f64 outputs.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Typed Absent + panic-freedom -->
    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Typed <code>Absent</code> and panic-freedom</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        Node output is now <code>Computed = Result&lt;f64, Absent&gt;</code> with explicit
        reasons (<code>WarmingUp</code>, <code>DivideByZero</code>, <code>FilteredOut</code>,
        <code>DomainError</code>). Production <code>unwrap</code> / <code>expect</code> /
        <code>panic</code> / <code>unreachable</code> removed; five clippy restriction lints
        locked at <code>deny</code>. Release profile enables overflow-checks. All eight
        <code>ValidationOptions</code> enforced with a new
        <code>TFloError::TimestampGapExceeded</code>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Phase 1 contracts -->
    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Phase 1 &mdash; async state &amp; checkpointing contracts</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        New <code>AsyncStateStore</code> trait (async <code>save</code> / <code>load</code>
        / <code>list_keys</code> / <code>save_batch</code> / <code>delete</code>) for
        network stores. <code>Checkpointer&lt;C, S, X&gt;</code> writes snapshot first,
        cursor last (crash-safe order), per-stage deadline + circuit breaker.
        <code>ShardRouter&lt;K&gt;</code> trait decouples key ownership from the engine.
        <code>Builder::fingerprint()</code> stamps a topology hash into each snapshot;
        fingerprint mismatch on restore is rejected. See
        <a href="/docs/contracts" class="text-primary hover:underline">Contracts</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- New primitives -->
    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Timers, <code>Deduplicator</code>, <code>Metrics</code></h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        Three first-class engine primitives land together. Timers: event-time, per-key
        heap, snapshot-safe (deterministic <code>(fire_ts, seq)</code> ordering).
        <code>Deduplicator&lt;K&gt;</code>: idempotent-sink primitive backed by
        <code>AsyncStateStore</code> &mdash; tflo's at-least-once + dedup answer to
        exactly-once. <code>Metrics</code>: pluggable trait fires on keyed-step latency,
        timer fires, checkpoint commit / failure, late-record drops; no-op default. See
        <a href="/docs/concepts" class="text-primary hover:underline">concepts</a> and
        <a href="/docs/advanced" class="text-primary hover:underline">advanced</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Phase 2-4 connectors -->
    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Phases 2&ndash;4 &mdash; connectors, sinks, Arrow</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Four new (or rewritten) integration crates:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        <li>
          <code>tflo-connect-kafka</code> rewritten with <code>KafkaShardRouter</code>,
          <code>AssignmentEpoch</code> monotonic counter for rebalance fencing, optional
          <code>rdkafka-backend</code> feature.
        </li>
        <li>
          <code>tflo-connect-mqtt</code> (new) for the edge:
          <code>BoundedSet</code> fixed-capacity QoS-2 dedup window (64 KiB cap),
          optional <code>rumqttc-backend</code> &mdash; pure Rust, cross-compiles cleanly to ARM.
        </li>
        <li>
          <code>tflo-sink-influx</code> (new): line-protocol builder,
          <code>Batcher</code> with hard <code>max_buffer_bytes</code> bound, pluggable
          <code>InfluxHttpClient</code> trait.
        </li>
        <li>
          <code>tflo-arrow</code> (new): <code>schema_fingerprint()</code>,
          <code>parquet</code> and <code>polars</code> feature flags, batch-replay
          sources and result sinks.
        </li>
        <li>
          <code>tflo-state-s3</code> rewritten as a direct <code>AsyncStateStore</code>
          implementation; <code>tflo-state-files</code> gained an async path via
          <code>spawn_blocking</code>.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Phase 6 reference deployment + docs -->
    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Reference deployment &amp; design docs</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        <code>tflo-examples/examples/iot-portal/</code> is the end-to-end reference: MQTT
        consume &rarr; conditioning &rarr; Kafka publish &rarr; central worker consume
        &rarr; Influx write &rarr; Parquet archive. Runs in CI with in-process mocks.
        Four new design docs: <a href="/docs/deployment-shapes" class="text-primary hover:underline">deployment shapes</a>,
        <a href="/docs/contracts" class="text-primary hover:underline">contracts</a>,
        <a href="/docs/non-goals" class="text-primary hover:underline">non-goals</a>, and
        <a href="/docs/interop-backlog" class="text-primary hover:underline">interop backlog</a>.
        See <a href="/docs/reference-deployment" class="text-primary hover:underline">reference deployment</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Hardening lints -->
    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Hardening lint backlog &mdash; 14 batches</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        <code>clippy::indexing_slicing</code>, <code>arithmetic_side_effects</code>,
        <code>integer_division</code>, <code>wildcard_enum_match_arm</code>,
        error-quality lints (<code>let_underscore_must_use</code>,
        <code>map_err_ignore</code>), and eight zero-hit production-grade lints all
        resolved. Centralized test exemptions via <code>cfg_attr(test)</code>. Golden
        55/55 fintech fixtures bit-exact; numeric-drift safeguard preserved. MSRV bumped
        from 1.85 to <strong class="text-white">1.88</strong>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Verification -->
    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Verification</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        <li><code>cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings</code> clean.</li>
        <li>42 test result groups pass (+20 new tests across Phases 1&ndash;4).</li>
        <li>Golden 55/55 TA-Lib fixtures intact.</li>
        <li><code>cargo run --example iot-portal</code> completes the full edge &rarr; cluster &rarr; sink &rarr; archive flow.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <div class="mt-16 p-6 rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-card">
      <p class="text-text-muted">
        <strong class="text-white">Canonical source:</strong>
        <a href="https://github.com/matt-cochran/tflo/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md" class="text-primary hover:underline">CHANGELOG.md</a>.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-muted mt-3">
        <strong class="text-white">Related:</strong>
        <a href="/positioning" class="text-primary hover:underline">Positioning</a>
        &middot;
        <a href="/docs/architecture" class="text-primary hover:underline">Crate architecture</a>
        &middot;
        <a href="/docs/reference-deployment" class="text-primary hover:underline">Reference deployment</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
